The paper deals with the computational complexity of a zero-player game on switch graphs, which involves analyzing the termination of the game and searching for a winning strategy. This involves techniques from computational geometry, graph theory, and algorithm design. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the game from a game-theoretic perspective, which could place it in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) category. Finally, the paper also involves designing efficient algorithms for solving the game, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
